This paper deals with a communication network and its optimization, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of buffer-aided relay and adaptive mode selection also involves System and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed protocol, which can be considered as a Computer Engineering (cs.CE) aspect.
